4. The SBBA Framework: Architecture and Design

The system is described categorically. The frozen oracle $\pi_0$ generates trajectories $\tau$ conditioned on the current tool graph $G$ and memory fabric $\mathcal{M}$. The self‑evaluation functional $\rho$ computes a reward from $\pi_0$’s outputs alone. This reward drives the phylogenetic forge $\Xi$, which produces a new population of tool graphs via tournament selection, mutation, crossover, and speciation. The memory fabric evolves concurrently via a coupled update rule (e.g., additive drift on a Hilbert space embedding or simply via the same genetic operators). Safety is enforced by composing each tool graph with an LTL monitor automaton and by restricting mutation/crossover to preserve monitor compatibility (see Section 5).

Perpetual loop (conceptual pseudocode):

```
Initialize frozen π₀, tool graph G₀, memory M₀, phylogeny Φ

while environment active:
    τ ← π₀.rollout(G, M)
    r ← ρ(τ)                     # black‑box self‑evaluation
    if r < threshold:
        (G, M) ← Ξ(G, M, r)       # phylogenetic evolution + memory adaptation
        Φ ← Φ ∪ {new nodes}
    deploy G, M for next step
```

Complexity per epoch is $O(T_{\text{rollout}} + T_{\text{eval}} + T_{\text{evolve}})$ under mild assumptions.

