A.4 Proof of Theorem 4.1 (Additive Drift)

Theorem (restated).
Under the conditions of Lemma 3.3.2,
\mathbb{E}[f_{k+1} - f_k \mid \mathcal{G}_k] \geq \frac{\mathrm{Var}(\rho)}{s}\left(1 - \frac{1}{n}\right) - L \cdot \mathbb{E}[d_{\text{edit}}].


If $\mathbb{E}[d_{\text{edit}}] < \frac{\mathrm{Var}(\rho)}{L s}(1-1/n)$, then the drift is positive.

Proof. This is a direct corollary of Lemma 3.3.2 by taking conditional expectation given the population at generation $k$ and noting that $\epsilon_{\text{mut}} = \mathbb{E}[d_{\text{edit}} \mid \mathcal{G}_k]$. The inequality holds for each realization, hence in expectation. ∎

